resh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/30/02 7:13:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Onegai Shimasu</span><hr size=1> In my martial arts class we say onegai shimasu at the begining of class. Sensei told us it means &quot;please assist me&quot;. But he also says that no translation is perfect. Hope that helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ucaserbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>caserbob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/30/02 8:21:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Onegai Shimasu</span><hr size=1> So in a nut shellit means help me?  Thanks for all the help.  Dozo. <p>"Squally Poo!"- My friend</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uaohjp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aoh jp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/30/02 8:54:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Onegai Shimasu</span><hr size=1> Ketsueki's explanation is quite fine about the case &quot;onagai shimasu&quot; is used for conventinal greetings.<br><br>This usage is a bit different from what I have been explaining so far. You could not find any adequate direct translation for &quot;onegai shimasu&quot; in the English world just like &quot;itadaki masu&quot;, &quot;gochisou sama&quot; or &quot;otsukare sama (deshita)&quot;.<br><br>&quot;onegai shimasu&quot; is quite a convenient greeting which means &quot;Please, help me&quot;. Everybody utters just before starting such a convention like a meeting exchanged  even between two persons.<br><br>In a meeting, &quot;yoroshiku onegai shi masu/itashi masu(politer)&quot; is most commonly used.<br> <p>aoh</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=714.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=714.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=714.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=714.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=714.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSFor